Rating: 4
I think this recipe is great. I've changed a few things slightly, taking many suggestions from the other reviewers - thank you all! Decrease the olive oil and balsamic vinegar (5 tablespoons olive oil to 4, and 3 tablespoons balsamic vinegar to 2). Use the white balsamic for the nicer color. Add extra garlic (I sautee it with the oil as the recipe indicates - haven't had any trouble with burning it as a few reviewers mentioned). Wait to add all the basil until after cooking. Plus, add some good cayenne pepper at the end to taste, which I think is the extra secret ingredient - I love that touch of spiciness. I've also tried adding a bit of cumin, which is nice too. I always use the fresh corn - it's so wonderful! seems like you can't go wrong with fresh corn in anything. Though haven't figured out how to cut the corn off the cob without make a bit of a mess (all part of the fun).

