Rating: 3
This is a really easy, tasty, and colorful salad. We served it in a blue bowl with a red towel underneath to hide the cold packs and took it to a 4th of July party. It received very good comments. Make this salad ahead it is best after chilling for a few hours so the flavors can blend. The most work involved is cutting the corn so a nice heavy knife is important. I used a bi-color corn which worked fine. I handled the dressing like many vinigarettes and halved the vinegar to the oil then whisked it before dressing the salad. Next time I will up the vinegar a bit.(I used 10 ears of corn and dressed it with 4 Tbls oil & 2 Tbls vinegar.

