This is a "tried and true" recipe I've been making it regularly since it's publication. I agree with the garlic tip - don't add it until the corn is almost done. I usually roast the corn on the BBQ and then finish in the pan with garlic. I also add all the basil at the end to prevent browning.

Rating: 3
For those who use frozen or canned corn, 6 ears is equivalent to 3 cups of corn. This was a great recipe; I've used it several times, always to rave reviews. I agree with the earlier comment, cook the garlic with the corn. Otherwise, it will brown. I also added red onion, salt and pepper to the finished dish and only used 2/3 of the balsamic vinegar. I used drained, canned diced tomatoes; the Red Gold brand is great. Also, the basil will darken if added to the heated dish. I waited until it had cooled so that the basil would keep its green color which I find more attractive.

Rating: 4
